OL,3,CFire chiefs told to reflect on
OL,4,Cpositions after 'serious failings of
OL,5,Cleadership'
OL,7,FThe report points to comments made by
OL,8,Fthe man responsible for oversight of
OL,9,FNorth Wales Fire, Dylan Rees, as an
OL,10,Fexample. In evidence to the committee,
OL,11,FMr Rees said: "We don't know if some
OL,12,Fof these 'complaints', in inverted
OL,13,Fcommas, are historic complaints with
OL,14,Fpeople who are dissatisfied with
OL,15,Fsomething that's happened."
OL,17,FHe added that he "disagreed completely
OL,18,Fwith some of the allegations that have
OL,19,Fappeared in the press".
